Mattias Scholle House is a historic home located at New Harmony, Posey County, Indiana. It was built about 1823, and is a two-story, Harmonist brick dwelling. It has a gable roof. It is an example of the standardized, mass-produced form of Rappite built dwellings.
It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1981. It is located in the New Harmony Historic District.


